thread.title: Man wanted in SE Portland slaying arrested in California
thread.title_full: Man wanted in SE Portland slaying arrested in California | OregonLive.com

author: Nuran Alteir | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Man wanted in SE Portland slaying arrested in California
text:
A man wanted in connection with a Southeast Portland homicide investigation has been arrested in California, police said Friday.
Members of the U.S. Marshals Fugitive Task Force and Sacramento County Sheriff's Office arrested Ricky Dean Seaman, 30, on Thursday, according to a news release from the Portland Police Bureau. He was wanted in connection with the slaying of 25-year-old Tyler Jeffrey Woods, who was gunned down near Southeast 132 nd Avenue and Bush Street at about 8 p.m. on Sept. 25.
At the time of the killing, Seaman was on supervised probation after pleading guilty to meth possession, according to court records.
Seaman has five prior felony convictions, including for second-degree robbery in 2010 and unauthorized use of a vehicle in 2006, 2007, 2008 and 2009. He has four misdemeanor convictions and 11 probation violations, according to court records.
Seaman was booked into the Sacramento County Jail pending extradition to Oregon, Sgt. Pete Simpson, a Portland police spokesman, wrote in a news release.
